{
	"name": "Town Portal",
	"type": "spell",
	"img": "icons/environment/settlement/gazebo.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>You take at least half a pound of pure water drawn from a fountain or body of water and sprinkle it on each target. Chanting, you fade from view and appear safely at your destination.</em></p><p><strong>Materials:</strong> You must use at least half a pound of water taken from a fountain or body of water within the chosen settlement.</p><p><strong>Teleportation Spell</strong></p><ul><li><p>When you finish casting this spell, your targets are teleported instantly to the edge of the same body of water within the chosen town, in a safe space.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><em>This spell fails immediately upon beginning to cast it if the body of water your water came from is gone, or if the town has been abandoned. Your GM may also rule that your chosen location does not count as a town if the location has fewer than 100 residents, but some very small towns should work with the spell. If this spell fails in this way, your spell slot is not expended.</em></p>",
